============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     HIV/AIDS
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HIV
Transmission:Sexual contact, blood
Symptoms:    Flu-like; then AIDS symptoms
Treatment:   Antiretroviral therapy (ART)
Deaths/yr:   0.65M
Vaccine:     No (in development)
Discovered:  1983

Disease:     COVID-19
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    SARS-CoV-2
Transmission:Respiratory droplets
Symptoms:    Fever, cough, loss of smell
Treatment:   Antivirals, supportive care
Deaths/yr:   5.0M
Vaccine:     Yes (mRNA vaccines)
Discovered:  2019

Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Game Theory
Category:   Economics
Definition: Study of strategic interactions between rational agents
Formula:    Nash equilibrium
Economist:  John Nash
Example:    OPEC cartel coordination; nuclear deterrence strategy

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

Concept:     Mixture of Experts
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Sparse model activating different expert subsets per token
Year:        2017
Researchers: Shazeer et al.
Applications:Large LLMs (Mixtral, rumored GPT-4)
Related:     Sparse activation, routing, scaling efficiency

Concept:     GAN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Generator vs discriminator adversarial training
Year:        2014
Researchers: Ian Goodfellow et al.
Applications:Image synthesis, deepfakes, augmentation
Related:     Mode collapse, discriminator, generator

